# ============================
# GLOBAL BEHAVIOR
# ============================
You must follow these rules for every code change, page creation, refactor, or UI update in this repository.

Always use Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Shadcn UI components.

Never invent custom CSS files.
Never create global CSS except for Tailwind layers already included.
Never output inline <style> blocks.
Never output arbitrary class names unless they are valid Tailwind utility classes.

All UI must follow the design system described below. No deviation.

# ============================
# DESIGN SYSTEM: LAYOUT
# ============================
All pages must follow this structural pattern:

<main className="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-10 space-y-10">
  <header className="space-y-1">
    <h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Page Title</h1>
    <p className="text-white/60 text-sm">Optional subtitle.</p>
  </header>

  <section className="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#060F1F]/60 p-6 shadow-inner shadow-black/30">
    <!-- Content -->
  </section>
</main>

Spacing scale must always use:
- gap-4, gap-6, gap-8
- p-4, p-6
- py-4, py-6, py-10

Never use margin/padding values outside this scale.

# ============================
# DESIGN SYSTEM: COMPONENTS
# ============================
Use ONLY the following UI primitives:

- Shadcn: Button, Card, Input, Label, Select, Dialog, Sheet, Separator, DropdownMenu, Tabs
- Tailwind utilities
- Lucide icons

NEVER use any other component library.
NEVER generate custom icons.
NEVER create new patterns not found in `/ui-reference`.

# ============================
# COLOR & STYLE RULES
# ============================
Use the dark theme colors that match the existing ledger UI:

Background layers:
- bg-[#050B18]
- bg-[#060F1F]/60
- bg-[#09142A]
- bg-white/5
- bg-white/10

Borders:
- border-white/5
- border-white/10

Text colors:
- text-white
- text-white/70
- text-white/60
- text-white/50

Accent colors:
- Primary: #2970FF
- Secondary: #5B9CFF

Never create new color tokens.
Never use random Tailwind arbitrary colors.

# ============================
# CHARTS
# ============================
When generating charts:
- Use Recharts ONLY.
- Use the color tokens already defined in existing chart components.
- Match the structure of SpendingBreakdownCard, SpendingComparisonChart, and CashFlowChart.

You must NOT create new chart styles.

# ============================
# PAGE GENERATION RULES
# ============================
When creating a new page:
1. Copy the page layout style from `/ui-reference/page-example.tsx`.
2. Use Shadcn Cards for content blocks.
3. Use uniform spacing and padding rules.
4. Use existing typography (never invent new font sizes outside Tailwind defaults).

# ============================
# DOMAIN-SPECIFIC RULES
# ============================
When working inside the ledger code:
- Follow existing function naming conventions.
- Follow the existing type structures.
- Do not modify helpers unless explicitly asked.
- Do not change currency formatting logic.
- Do not change date formatting utilities.

# ============================
# NAVIGATION & FEATURE RULES
# ============================
- Never invent new navigation items, routes, or pages. Only use nav items, labels, and hrefs that already exist in the current file or are explicitly requested in the prompt.
- Never add sidebar items like Store, Team, Inbox, Upgrade, or similar unless they already exist in the codebase or are explicitly requested.
- When refactoring shells or layouts, preserve the existing navigation semantics (same items, same routes, same active logic).
- Do not introduce new feature sections (e.g. storage usage, upgrade banners, marketing cards) unless explicitly asked for.

# ============================
# RESTYLING VS PRODUCT CHANGES
# ============================
- When asked to "refactor", "restyle", or "upgrade" UI, only change layout, spacing, Tailwind classes, and visual hierarchy. Do NOT change business logic, routing, or domain behavior.
- Do not change or invent labels, copy, or text content unless explicitly requested. Preserve the existing wording and meaning.
- Do not add or remove interactive elements (buttons, inputs, filters, toggles) unless explicitly requested. Existing controls may be rearranged or visually upgraded, but not semantically altered.
- Treat components in /ui-reference as style and structure references only. Do NOT copy their labels, dummy menu items, or fake features into production code.
- When in doubt, prefer minimal visual changes that keep the current UX intact rather than introducing new patterns or elements.

# ============================
# STRICT MODE
# ============================
If ambiguous instructions appear, always choose the option that:
- Follows the UI reference folder,
- Uses Shadcn,
- Uses Tailwind,
- Stays minimal and consistent,
- Matches the existing dark-SaaS aesthetic.

Never generate creative layout variants unless explicitly instructed.